Example of stack of layers of suitable and unsuitable conditions for species

Source: R/data_documentation.R
sp_layers.Rd

An object of class RasterStack containing information about suitable and unsuitable conditions for five species.

Format

RasterStack with 109 rows, 182 columns, 19838 cells, and 5 layers:

RasterLayer

suitable (1) and unsuitable (0) conditions

Examples

sp_layers <- raster::stack(system.file("extdata/sp_layers.tif",
                           package = "biosurvey"))

sp_layers

#> class      : RasterStack 
#> dimensions : 109, 182, 19838, 5  (nrow, ncol, ncell, nlayers)
#> resolution : 0.1666667, 0.1666667  (x, y)
#> extent     : -117.1324, -86.79904, 14.56388, 32.73055  (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)
#> crs        : +proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs 
#> names      : sp_layers.1, sp_layers.2, sp_layers.3, sp_layers.4, sp_layers.5 
#> min values :           0,           0,           0,           0,           0 
#> max values :           1,           1,           1,           1,           1 
#>
